Package com.cafean.client.values

Class AccessorType

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.client.values.AccessorType
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    RealAccessorType
    public abstract class AccessorType
extends java.lang.Object
    Implementations of AccessorType act as intermediate containers for for categories of Accessors. It can be used to create a tree hierarchy of categories via the getChildren() method.

      • getChildren

        public abstract java.util.List<AccessorType> getChildren()
        Gets a List of child AccessorTypes.The results of this method, combined with the recursive results of getChildren on the AccessorTypes in the results, is used to form a tree hierarchy of Accessor categories. Implementations shall return a non-null List, although the List may be empty.

        Because of the frequency with which getChildren will be called, the result should generally be cached. The result should also be a List implementation the implements RandomAccess for fast access to nodes by index.

        Returns:
        List of child AccessorTypes

      • getAccessors

        public abstract java.util.List<Accessor> getAccessors()
        Gets the Accessors associated with the type. Implementations shall return a non-null List, although the result may be empty.

        When implementing this method, consider that AccessorTypes may be instantiated often, while this method will (in general) only be called sporadically. Implementations should retrieve the Accessors from the model (in the case of components and sub-blocks that implement Accessor) or instantiate new instances (in the case of proxy Accessors).

        Returns:
        the Accessors associated with the type
